<!-- Help Modal -->
<div id="help-text" class="modal">
  <div class="modal-content">
    <h4>Instructions</h4>
    <h5>How to write Scribl-Er</h5>
    <p>Welcome to writing Scribl-Er. If you know how to write HTML, then you know Scribl-Er. All you need now is the syntax.</p>
    <p>The concept is the same as putting Python and HTML together. There are no brackets and white-space is important. Every tag is followed with a colon [:] and all displayed text is surrounded by double quotes ["]. Inline tags, such as spans, can be pushed inline using double parentheses [((span))]. To enclose tags inside of other tags, indent using the tab key. To force close a tag, you can use the semi-colon [;].</p>
    <p><strong>Example</strong></p>
    <code>
      <p>
        <span>div id="main-content":</span><br>
        <span style="margin-left: 20px">h1: "Example Heading"</span><br>
        <span style="margin-left: 20px">hr:</span><br>
        <span style="margin-left: 20px">div id="example-code":</span><br>
          <span style="margin-left: 40px">p class="center-align":</span><br>
            <span style="margin-left: 60px">"This is some example text to show off Scribl-Er. You can use ((em: "inline")) characters to contain tags and text. You could also use syntax " strong: "like this"; " to also inline content."</span><br>
        <span style="margin-left: 20px">p: "Just remember that white-space is important. This content is not contained with the #example-code div."</span><br>
      </p>
    </code>
  </div>
  <div class="modal-footer">
    <a href="#!" class="modal-action modal-close waves-effect btn-flat">Close</a>
  </div>
</div>

